OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be a largely dry and
OL,6,Fcloudy day but with bright or sunny
OL,7,Fspells breaking through, as well as
OL,8,Fthe odd shower possible. Light winds.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FA dry start to the evening
OL,11,Fwith bright spells but soon turning
OL,12,Fcloudier with rain spreading into
OL,13,Fsouthern areas. Cloudy overnight with
OL,14,Foutbreaks of rain, possibly heavy, for
OL,15,Fall parts.
OL,16,
OL,17,CMonday:FCloudy with showery rain,
OL,18,Fwhich will be heavy at times, for much
OL,19,Fof the morning and afternoon. Turning
OL,20,Fdrier with clear spells developing in
OL,21,Fthe evening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
